The Insider from TravelocitycomSavings Abroad Dear Tana Spring is nearly here and that means its time to think seriously about planning your next trip whether its for spring break summer vacation or just because youre tired of being cooped up in the house Whatever your reason for traveling consider going a little further afield this time International travel isnt as expensive or as complicated as you might think And as always were here to help Travelocitycom has loads of online information to help you decide where to goand great deals to help put your trip within the reach of your budget Its a big world out thereits time to discover it In this issue Featured This Month Win a Trip to Scotland Barcelona Mexico Copenhagen Dublin Brazil Rome Travelocitys Been There Todays Real Deals Site Features FREE Issue of Travelocity Magazine Travelers Network Traveler Reviews Tips Advice Travel Tips Special Offers Spring Skiing Specials Le Mridien Exclusive Offer Exclusive Offer from LimoCenter FEATURED THIS MONTH Win a Trip to Scotland Enter to win a trip to Scotland One lucky winner and guest will receive the vacation of their choice a golf vacation a hiking tour of Scotland or a romantic getaway Dont miss out enter by April Barcelona Save on your airfare when you pay with a MasterCard Barcelona surely ranks among Europes most beautiful and artistic cities Picasso called this city home for a time and theres a museum devoted to Mir as well But the most obvious works of art are the examples of architecture unique to Barcelona The eccentric genius Antoni Gaud erected a number of eyecatching buildings here including his unfinished masterpiece the Sagrada Familia cathedral Also worth seeing is the old gothic quarter full of postcardperfect winding alleys and hidden shops and galleries Far from living in its past however Barcelona offers plenty in the way of modern pleasures of dining and barhopping as well Mexico Save per person to Mexico Whether its culture or beaches margaritas or Mayan artifacts that you seek theres a vacation for everyone in Mexico From the teeming streets of Mexico city to the jungle ruins of ChichnItza adventure abounds Of course so does relaxation Beach resorts such as Cancn and Cozumel provide as much sun and surf as you could ever want You can also escape the crowds in more offthebeatenpath locations such as Zihuatanejo and Mazatlan Whatever youre looking for in a vacation youll find it in Mexico Copenhagen Save on your airfare when you pay with a MasterCard Copenhagen isnt Amsterdam but it is one of Europes livelier cities Maybe its the need to cut loose after the long dark winters Maybe its the glorious nearly endless spring and summer days Whatever it is Danes certainly know how to have fun And whatever your idea of fun is youll find it in Copenhagen From the timeless amusement of the worldfamous Tivoli Gardens to the longest pedestrian shopping street in Europe to the continents largest jazz festival Copenhagen makes for a delightful vacation Dublin Great fares to Ireland from Aer Lingusonly on Travelocity Dublin is a shining example of how a city can turn its fortunes around in less than a decade Once an overlooked corner of the British Isles think The Commitments this Celtic Tiger has transformed itself into a beautiful vibrant city Attractions such as Trinity College St Patricks Cathedral and of course the Guinness Brewery still pull in visitors as they always did But today shopping dining and night life are also firstrate and the city attracts much of the same wellheeled funloving The Insider from TravelocitycomSavings Abroad Dear Tana Spring is nearly here and that means its time to think seriously about planning your next trip whether its for spring break summer vacation or just because youre tired of being cooped up in the house Whatever your reason for traveling consider going a little further afield this time International travel isnt as expensive or as complicated as you might think And as always were here to help Travelocitycom has loads of online information to help you decide where to goand great deals to help put your trip within the reach of your budget Its a big world out thereits time to discover it In this issue Featured This Month Win a Trip to Scotland Barcelona Mexico Copenhagen Dublin Brazil Rome Travelocitys Been There Todays Real Deals Site Features FREE Issue of Travelocity Magazine Travelers Network Traveler Reviews Tips Advice Travel Tips Special Offers Spring Skiing Specials Le Mridien Exclusive Offer Exclusive Offer from LimoCenter FEATURED THIS MONTH Win a Trip to Scotland Enter to win a trip to Scotland One lucky winner and guest will receive the vacation of their choice a golf vacation a hiking tour of Scotland or a romantic getaway Dont miss out enter by April Barcelona Save on your airfare when you pay with a MasterCard Barcelona surely ranks among Europes most beautiful and artistic cities Picasso called this city home for a time and theres a museum devoted to Mir as well But the most obvious works of art are the examples of architecture unique to Barcelona The eccentric genius Antoni Gaud erected a number of eyecatching buildings here including his unfinished masterpiece the Sagrada Familia cathedral Also worth seeing is the old gothic quarter full of postcardperfect winding alleys and hidden shops and galleries Far from living in its past however Barcelona offers plenty in the way of modern pleasures of dining and barhopping as well Mexico Save per person to Mexico Whether its culture or beaches margaritas or Mayan artifacts that you seek theres a vacation for everyone in Mexico From the teeming streets of Mexico city to the jungle ruins of ChichnItza adventure abounds Of course so does relaxation Beach resorts such as Cancn and Cozumel provide as much sun and surf as you could ever want You can also escape the crowds in more offthebeatenpath locations such as Zihuatanejo and Mazatlan Whatever youre looking for in a vacation youll find it in Mexico Copenhagen Save on your airfare when you pay with a MasterCard Copenhagen isnt Amsterdam but it is one of Europes livelier cities Maybe its the need to cut loose after the long dark winters Maybe its the glorious nearly endless spring and summer days Whatever it is Danes certainly know how to have fun And whatever your idea of fun is youll find it in Copenhagen From the timeless amusement of the worldfamous Tivoli Gardens to the longest pedestrian shopping street in Europe to the continents largest jazz festival Copenhagen makes for a delightful vacation Dublin Great fares to Ireland from Aer Lingusonly on Travelocity Dublin is a shining example of how a city can turn its fortunes around in less than a decade Once an overlooked corner of the British Isles think The Commitments this Celtic Tiger has transformed itself into a beautiful vibrant city Attractions such as Trinity College St Patricks Cathedral and of course the Guinness Brewery still pull in visitors as they always did But today shopping dining and night life are also firstrate and the city attracts much of the same wellheeled funloving crowd that used to head directly to London Rome and other urbane European capitals Brazil Save on your South American vacation The bad news is youve missed Carnival The good news is the drunken crowds have all gone home and this is an excellent time to see the real Rio de Janeiro Rio is one of the most exotic cities in the Western Hemisphere a place where the infectious rhythms of samba and bossa nova are in the air and the beach is a way of life Of course theres more to Brazil than just this one city The Amazon jungle beckons the adventurous and the countrys Iguassu Falls are a mustsee for nature lovers Discover the passionate way of life that is Brazil Rome Save with British Airways to Rome Its said that all roads lead to Rome and you owe it to yourself to test that theory one of these days Europes most ancient city offers an exciting blend of the historical and the modern Sip cappuccino next to monuments older than Christianity Shop for shoes along streets once trod by emperors Shop for postcards in the shadow of the Sistine Chapel Few places on earth boast this concentration of art and history and fewer still wrap it a package as beguiling as Rome Travelocitys Been There about our adventures then make your plans to go there too TODAYS REAL DEALS Monumental March Savings to London For as little as oneway from New York JFK you could spend March in London US cities are
